claim.claim-text:
A method for secure touch screen input comprising:
receiving from a touch screen an indication of a touch event on a predetermined enablement area on said touch screen;
receiving from said touch screen an indication of a touch event on an interface element presented on said touch screen associated with a command;
verifying that said interface element touch event occurs at an overlapping time with said enablement area touch event; and
when said touch events occur at overlapping times, performing said command.

A system for secure touch screen input, comprising:
a touch screen identifying touch events of a user;
at least one interface element presented on said touch screen associated with a command;
a predetermined enablement area on said touch screen;
a processor performing said command after receiving from said touch screen an indication of a touch event on said enablement area and a touch event on said at least one interface element that occurs at an overlapping time.

A computer program product for secure touch screen input, comprising:
a computer readable storage medium having stored thereon:
first program instructions executable by a processor to cause said processor to defining an enablement area on a touch screen;
second program instructions executable by said processor to cause said processor to receive from said touch screen an indication of a touch event on a said enablement area;
third program instructions executable by said processor to cause said processor to receive from said touch screen an indication of a touch event on an interface element presented on said touch screen associated with a command;
forth program instructions executable by said processor to cause said processor to verify that said interface element touch event occurs at an overlapping time with said enablement area touch event; and
fifth program instructions executable by said processor to cause said processor to perform said command when said touch events are occur at overlapping times.
